<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc42fba26-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s8137"><num value="8137">§ 8137.</num><heading> State control of operations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as otherwise specifically provided, nothing in this subchapter shall be construed as conferring on any Federal officer or employee the right to exercise any supervision or control over the administration, personnel, maintenance, or operation of any State home for which facilities are constructed or acquired with assistance received under this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc42fba27-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/88/450/s4/a">Pub. L. 88–450, § 4(a)</ref>, <date date="1964-08-19">Aug. 19, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/503">78 Stat. 503</ref>, § 5037; amended <ref href="/us/pl/98/528/tI/s105/5">Pub. L. 98–528, title I, § 105(5)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2690">98 Stat. 2690</ref>; renumbered § 8137, <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s402/b/1">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 402(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/238">105 Stat. 238</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
